<paragraph blockId="28.[136,1452,989,1389]" pageId="28" pageNumber="89">Main thallus with polygonal cells, 4.4–5.2 µm diam. Pseudofilaments radiating into substrate, 30.8–78.0 µm length, branched, uniseriate. Sheath firm, hyaline, conspicuous, non-lamellate, smooth. Middle cells of pseudofilaments quadratic to rectangular, 1.9–3.6 × 3.3–9.0 µm. Apical cells of pseudofilaments tortuous, round ends, 1.9–2.8 × 10.6– 17.0 µm. Baeocytes produced by the main thallus, more than 20 per cell, 1.2–1.6 µm diam. Cell content homogenous, rosy to purple-brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="89" type="description">
