</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[136,1452,989,1389]" pageId="28" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1213,1239]" pageId="28" pageNumber="89">Notes:</emphasis>
—The habitat and morphology of the colonies and cells of the Brazilian population are similar to those described for 
<taxonomicName authority="Al-Thukair &amp; Golubic (1996: 84)" authorityName="Al-Thukair &amp; Golubic" authorityPageNumber="84" authorityYear="1996" box="[297,1071,1251,1277]" class="Cyanophyceae" family="Hyellaceae" genus="Hyella" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Pleurocapsales" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" phylum="Cyanobacteria" rank="variety" species="caespitosa" variety="arbuscula">
<emphasis box="[297,499,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="89">Hyella caespitosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[561,673,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="89">arbuscula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Thukair, A. A. &amp; Golubic, S." box="[682,1071,1251,1277]" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" pagination="83 - 91" refId="ref18300" refString="Al-Thukair, A. A. &amp; Golubic, S. (1996) Characterization of Hyella caespitosa var. arbuscula var. nov. (Cyanophyta, Cyanobacteria) from shoaling ooid sand grains, Arabian Gulf. Beihefte zur Nova Hedwigia 112: 83 - 91." type="journal article" year="1996">Al-Thukair &amp; Golubić (1996: 84)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the dimensions of all structures were smaller.
</paragraph>
